snippet.textDisplay: My sister is a single mother of 2 who is an independent contractor at a tattoo shop. She scrapes and saves every dime she makes to keep a roof over their head and food in their stomach. She saved up $3200 over the course of 2 years to buy a reliable 4WD suv to get to and from work (a 32 mile Commute) only to have her purse (with all the money in it) stolen from her by the dealership she was planning on buying the car from. She left her purse in the truck after test driving it, and when the porter went to park the jeep he took the money and threw the purse in the trash. Of course we couldn't prove any of this. So my family all worked together to scrape up what we could (roughly 1200) and bought her an old, rough jeep cherokee. My point is the same as most of the people on here. I love most of your videos when something gets broken from you out having fun, more power to ya, but when you post a video of you purposefully destroying a $100,000 truck just because you can, it's like a slap in the face to those of us that have to put everything we have into our vehicles... It's just wasteful.
